<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" Description="This caldef defines the calibrations in GIS-608 for Global A.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>6</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>10/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Maintained the following updates as pertains to the GIS608_LVDS_I2C.caldef file: Able to contain calibrations defined in the GIS-608 to one caldef. With that said, removed previously GIS-608 caldef/enumdef files from initial MY19 CAL Database Version 3.0.0 (initial MY19 release) and now have all of the calibrations for the GIS-608 defined in the GIS608_LVDS_I2C.caldef/GIS608_LVDS_I2C.enumdef files. Also updated calibration descriptions for all of the calibrations in this caldef file to include reference in the definition to which section in the GIS-608 defines the requirements for this calibration for addtional clarity. Deleted the calibration called TOUCH_CONTROLLER_IDENTIFIER, since it has not yet been determined if this is needed as a calibration nor if it is what model year it would be needed for. Also added usage of Low Radio for the calibration called ICS_CONTROLS_ON_LVDS_I2C since this was confirmed by Johnathan Beckwith (MY19 I3L Software Lead) and the rest of the Low Radio team via email correspondence on 10/19/2016 this calibration was needed for Low Radio too. </Description>
    <Author>Reno Ramsey</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS608_LVDS_I2C.caldef, added GEM usage to the ICS_CONTROLS_ON_LVDS_I2C calibration within this caldef. Since this calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application. Note, excluded adding GEM usage to the F-Ten Low Radio only specific legacy calibrations within this caldef since these calibrations are only be used for the F-Ten Radio supplier, which does support the GEM.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>09/18/2018</Date>
    <Description>Per the request of LOW radio, LOW and GEM was added to the USAGE statement for TOUCH_CONTROLLER_CALIBRATION_FILE and ENABLE_TOUCH_CONTROLLER_CALIBRATION_UPDATES cals.</Description>
    <Author>Ibnul Khan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration indicates the encoder technology used for the volume.  For a detailed description see GIS-608-300 ICS Controls I2C Memory Map." Name="VOLUME_ENCODER_TECHNOLOGY" References="GIS-608-300 ICS Controls I2C Memory Map Data Address 0x11" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_97V7gHxREeaHHOy4fZEGwA</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>_3V1SAHxPEeaHHOy4fZEGwA</EnumID>
      <Value>0</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="This file contains the touch controller calibration and tuning file.  This file can be loaded and flashed into the touch controller from the CSM. This calibration defines the specific touch controller IC used in the ICS.  This calibration  contains the calibration/tuning file for the touch controller.  For additional description see GIS-608-100 Calibration Data and Tuning." Name="TOUCH_CONTROLLER_CALIBRATION_FILE" References="See GIS-608-100 Calibration Data and Tuning" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_6jb8IBIEEea05achkF2wgw</CalID>
    <Type>BinaryFile</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>09/18/2018</Date>
      <Description>Added LOW and GEM to the Usage</Description>
      <Author>Ibnul Khan</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <BinaryFile>
      <Filename>DD080ZA_01A_10AA_V03_20160509.xcfg</Filename>
      <Data></Data>
      <Length>56962</Length>
      <Checksum>3436184834</Checksum>
    </BinaryFile>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="When true this calibration indicates that the ICS controls information is on LVDS_I2C.  When false the ICS controls information will be on LIN(GA) or CAN5(GB).  For additional description see GIS-608-030 I2C Touch Controller &amp; Controls Communication to/from the ICS and the CSM." Name="ICS_CONTROLS_ON_LVDS_I2C" References="See GIS-608-030 I2C Touch Controller &amp; Controls Communication to/from the ICS and the CSM" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_LIopQBIEEea05achkF2wgw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>10/24/2016</Date>
      <Description>Added usage of Low Radio for the calibration called ICS_CONTROLS_ON_LVDS_I2C since this was confirmed by Johnathan Beckwith (MY19 I3L Software Lead) and the rest of the Low Radio team via email correspondence on 10/19/2016 this calibration was needed for Low Radio too. </Description>
      <Author>Reno Ramsey</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>4</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="When true this calibration indicates that the touch information is on LVDS_I2C.  When false the touch information will be on LIN(GA) or CAN5(GB).  For additional description see GIS-608-030 I2C Touch Controller &amp; Controls Communication to/from the ICS and the CSM." Name="TOUCH_CONTROLLER_ON_LVDS_I2C" References="See GIS-608-030 I2C Touch Controller &amp; Controls Communication to/from the ICS and the CSM" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_eLYzYBICEea05achkF2wgw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="When true this calibration indicates the touch controller calibration/tuning file (note: defined by the calibration called TOUCH_CONTROLLER_CALIBRATION_FILE) in the touch controller should be updated.  When false the touch controller should not be updated. For additional description see GIS-608-030 I2C Touch Controller &amp; Controls Communication to/from the ICS and the CSM.  " Name="ENABLE_TOUCH_CONTROLLER_CALIBRATION_UPDATES" References="See GIS-608-030 I2C Touch Controller &amp; Controls Communication to/from the ICS and the CSM" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_WrIjcBIBEea05achkF2wgw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>09/18/2018</Date>
      <Description>Added LOW and GEM to the Usage</Description>
      <Author>Ibnul Khan</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>false</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
</caldef:CalDefinitionFile>